Ella Dawson, a recent graduate of Wesleyan University, was diagnosed with herpes two years ago and has been dropping the 'herpes bomb' about six months .
In her essay for Women's Health Mag, Dawson recalls meeting a boy at a party who offered her a sip of his beer .
'I had seen in the flesh what a simple "I have herpes" could do when said fearlessly, without shame,' she said .